<p class="newssubhead_t1">U.S. FARMERS PESSIMISTIC: POLL     </p>
<p>NEW YORK / U.S. farmers are pessimistic about their current economic situation, says a new survey-based index produced by DTN/The Progressive Farmer, an agricultural news service.</p>
<p>The initial survey produced a score of 34.2 for the present economic situation, Progressive Farmer said Monday. Any score below 50 indicates pessimism, says the service, a unit of Madrid-based Telvent GIT SA. The index rises to 36.9 when farmers are asked about expectations, the news service said.</p>
<p>Livestock producers were more bearish than crop growers, with a score of 26.8 compared with 31.2. Ranchers were more optimistic on expectations with a score of 40.1 compared with 35.6 for crop farmers.</p>
